spanGrp.span: My name and of my father
jina langu na la baba yangu
I'm called Barandi and am of Shawuuri
mimi ninaitwa barandi na ni wa shauri
In the old days I grew up in Gileewdabeshta
aa geejiilaan mateeseed qayaaj ab qahaany aa mandan
And when I was born there were no problems
na nilipo zaliwa kwetu mateso niliyopata hakuna
ha gagudgut aa iimuch aa gaw qeend
Well, it was like this and later when I went to marry
basi ikaw hivyo na baadaye nilipoenda kuolewa
meaw gwargw ha qateaseak ab hiji
After he died, well, I struggled a lot then
baada ya mzee kufariki basi nikatesekea hapo
qanyaasc durmaanaat ha aa gajiil aa gataand qareed gwargweed dita
I became pregnant and gave birth to a child and I was with that elder
nikapata mimba nikazaa na bado nipo kwa yule mzee
qameaw jaft qamiinyaan jaft ab hij aa
The child pass away, the child became sick then
gohilaaj abi hij aa daw sibdarees uliyaan
The child was fainting often until I went to the Oldeani hospital
akawa anazimiaga hapo hadi nikaenda hospitali ya oldeani
gamuuch aa gabiigw aa qameaw jaft
Later and I returned and my child died
After my child died, well, I came
baada ya mtoto kufariki basi nikaja
aa gaftaad siku kidoago aa gaw qeend
I stayed there and went to marry
I married with that elder, elder Gidang'ol
'nikaolewa na huyo mzee ambaye ni mzee gidang''ol'
I came to struggle with hunger then
aha muuch qaweadaan aseet ha ab hiji
And later God helped me then
qang'oony gisirjaand aa qabarj ng'any aa
I took my hoe and farmed until
And that time there was a lot of water, no one would pray for it
na kipindi kile maji yalikuwa bado ni mengi hayaombwagwi
You go down to the river
mandan ar shiid gibiit jeed beeg aa giitiin beeg aa gileayd ukweadaang'w
There was no problem, you would crouch in the water and open the water and water your field
hakuna shida unashuka kwenye maji unayafunga maji na kunyeshea shamba lako
ha ab hij mandan ar shiid gang'aad deebugees aa qaleaqleaq aa
And then there were no problems, I took care of my children and protected them
na hapo hakuna shida niliwakuza watoto wangu na niliwatunza
So that even they can help me
ha qayaaj shiidan aa qoos aa qohaab
Well, I got a problem recently, and after recovering
basi nikala shida ha juzi baada ya kupona
quuwari gageesh musei gwad deebuug buneeda ar deebuug gageshi
The elder married and brought three children and even the children married
mzee akaoa akaleta watoto wa watu na hata watoto wakaoa
Well, they were having problems, the women dispersed
basi wakawa wanateseka teseka wanawake wakatawanyika
Because of problems in the home
qwadaar gadeemg haqawuuny dahangayiikaad aa qo qamn ar qamn gatand jeed shiid gadeemg mandan gandaw geew
Well, the women dispersed and I came to have problems until now, I've still got problems, the women have scattered
basi wanawake wakatawanyiika na mimi nikaja kuteseka na mpak sasa hivi bado nipo kwenye shida wanawake wameshatawanyika
And it's not that I haven't given birth
And it's not that people haven't married
aa shideed and jeed aa nihi qamn
And the problem I had was this
na shida niliopo ndani yake ni hiyo sasa
aa qamn ar qamn ha gatayawuudaaj ab ng'asheeg
And until now I am still crying because
na hat mpaka sasa bado ninalia kwa sababu
I am living on my own
aa shiideed qamn ha and jeeda
This is the problem, which I have
na ndiyo shida ambayo sasa hivi nipo ndani yake
